<opener><address><addrLine>R.N. Barracks</addrLine>
<addrLine>Chatham</addrLine></address>
<dateline><date>31.5.16</date></dateline>

<salute>Sir,</salute></opener>
<p>I should be obliged if you 
<lb/>would let me know whether any action
<lb/> is being taken with regard to my letter
<lb/>of 5th inst,asking for compensation in
<lb/>regard to the travelling expenses of my
<lb/>servant, Violet Williams.  I received an
<lb/>acknowledgement of its receipt.</p>

<salute>Yours faithfully</salute>
<signed>J. Smith Wright
<lb/>Lt-Commander RN</signed>

<address>The Secretary
<lb/>Dublin Castle.</address>

<note>Under Secretary
<lb/>Submitted for directions as to reply
<lb/>to be sent <unclear>CWG</unclear>
<lb/>1-6-'16</note>

<note>Reply that their <sic>Excies</sic> are unable to recognize 
<lb/>claim against public funds for compensation in 
<lb/>the  <sic>circs.</sic> represented.<lb/>RC<lb/>1.6.16<lb/></note>
        
    

    
                </body>
            </text>

        
            
        

         

    </group>
</text>
     

